# AuraSpear SOC Frontend — Cursor Rules

## Tech Stack
- Next.js 16 + React 19 + TypeScript 5 (App Router)
- Tailwind CSS v4 + shadcn/ui (new-york style)
- @tanstack/react-query for server state
- react-hook-form + zod for forms
- Zustand for global client state
- next-intl for i18n (6 locales: en, es, fr, it, ar, de)
- next-themes for dark/light mode
- Axios (pre-configured instance with token refresh)
- lucide-react for icons
- sonner (Toast) + sweetalert2 (SweetAlertDialog) for notifications

## Absolute Rules — NEVER Violate

1. NEVER use `any` — use `unknown`, generics, or proper types
2. NEVER disable ESLint rules — no `// eslint-disable`, no `@ts-ignore`, no `@ts-expect-error`
3. NEVER use static Tailwind color classes for semantic colors — use status/severity class system (text-status-warning, bg-severity-critical, etc.)
4. NEVER use `<table>` directly — use `<DataTable>` from `@/components/common/DataTable`
5. NEVER use `==` or `!=` — always `===` and `!==`
6. NEVER use `var` — use `const` (preferred) or `let`
7. NEVER use `!` (non-null assertion) — use `if`, `??`, `?.`
8. NEVER use `console.log` — only `console.warn` and `console.error`
9. NEVER hardcode user-facing text — always use `t()` from `next-intl`
10. NEVER use string concatenation — use template literals
11. NEVER use raw HTML `<select>`, `<input>`, `<textarea>` — use shadcn/ui components
12. NEVER add `// eslint-disable-next-line` — fix the code instead
13. NEVER put const/interface/enum/type inside component files — enums → `src/enums/`, types → `src/types/`, constants → `src/lib/constants/`
14. NEVER put custom hooks inside component files — hooks → `src/hooks/`
15. NEVER put utility functions inside component files — utils → `src/lib/`
16. NEVER use `text-red-*`, `text-green-*`, `bg-white`, `bg-gray-*` — use semantic classes (text-destructive, text-status-success, bg-card, bg-muted)
17. NEVER use `dark:` prefix for colors — CSS variables handle dark mode automatically
18. NEVER filter/search client-side — all filtering must go through backend API with query params
19. NEVER use string literal unions — always use enums from `src/enums/`

## File Organization
- Enums: `src/enums/<domain>.enum.ts` (barrel export via index.ts)
- Types: `src/types/<domain>.types.ts` (barrel export via index.ts)
- Constants: `src/lib/constants/<domain>.constants.ts`
- Hooks: `src/hooks/use<Feature>.ts`
- Services: `src/services/<feature>.service.ts`
- Stores: `src/stores/<feature>.store.ts`

## Component Patterns
- Server Components by default, `'use client'` only when needed
- Use `PageHeader` from `@/components/common` for page headers
- Use `Toast` from `@/components/common` for notifications
- Use `SweetAlertDialog` from `@/components/common` for confirmations
- Use `Badge` from `@/components/ui/badge` for status indicators

## Error Handling
- All API errors: `Toast.error(tErrors(getErrorKey(error)))` pattern
- Import `getErrorKey` from `@/lib/api-error`
- Backend always returns `messageKey` for i18n

## i18n
- Client: `const t = useTranslations('namespace')`
- Server: `const t = await getTranslations('namespace')`
- Every new feature MUST include translations in ALL 6 locale files
- Error keys: `errors.<module>.<specificAction>`

## Formatting
- No semicolons, single quotes, 2-space indent, 100 char width
- Trailing comma: es5, arrow parens: avoid, end of line: lf
- Tailwind classes auto-sorted by prettier plugin

## Search/Filter/Pagination
- Debounce search inputs (400ms)
- Reset page to 1 on filter change
- Use `placeholderData: keepPreviousData` in useQuery
- Pass `isFetching` (not `isLoading`) to DataTable loading prop
- Query keys must include all filter params
